  "lyrics": "What don't you believe Do you think I'm here to deceive\nLead you astray have my way then rise up early leave\nWhat didn't you hear What part sounded in sincere\nIf it was when I dared to call you rare perhaps i can make it clear\nI'll try to explain the Best that I can\nUsing only the thoughts of the common man , There comes an age, there comes a time\nwhen treasures get hard to find\nAnd you girl, you've been around the world You like Steve Earle\nI swear on heaven, on everything That you're my kind of girl\nNow there's a matter we need to discuss It's not a druther, but I know that we must\nIf you're looking for jewelry I'll finding a brewery on the next available bus\nI hope this isn't the end I'd be happy if you labeled us friends\nIf every once in a while you'd help me find my smile\nAgain and again I'll try to explain\nThe best that I can Using only these thoughts of this coming rain\nComes an age, there comes a time When treasures get hard to find\nYeah, treasures get hard to find\nYou've been around the world and you like Steve Earle I swear girl, you're my kind\nYou've been around the world and you like Steve Earle I swear girl, you're my kind\nYou've been around the world Loving that Earle\nI swear you're my, I swear you're my kind of girl, yeah\nI'll try to explain The best that I can\nUsing only these thoughts of this common man aye!\nComes an age, there comes a time When treasures get hard to find\nYeah, treasures get hard to find\nYou've been around the world and you like Steve Earle\nI swear baby, you're my kind of girl\nYou like Steve Earle, I swear you're my kind of girl\nI swear baby, you're my kind of girl",
